textAnnotations.description:
For some reason the orderlier had forgotten
to switch on the lights; there was no colour -
physical features were distinguishable solely by
gradations of silvery greyness. Even the snow -
capped summit of Mount Planc, seven miles
below, was not recognisable among the host
of lower peaks . The screen of the air-to-air-
radar glowed. Eccasionally minute spots
flickered
across
its surface, but there whe
was
no permanent image.
